🧪 PROMETHEUS QUICK CHECK QUERIES
👉 Use in Prometheus → Graph → Table mode
________________________________________
1. Check if containers are being scraped
container_last_seen
👉 Shows all active containers (basic sanity check)
________________________________________
2. Count total containers
count(container_last_seen)
👉 Confirms how many containers Prometheus sees
________________________________________
3. CPU usage (raw counter)
container_cpu_usage_seconds_total
👉 Verifies CPU metric exists (before rate calculation)
________________________________________
4. Memory usage
container_memory_usage_bytes
👉 Shows memory used per container
________________________________________
5. Network receive
container_network_receive_bytes_total
👉 Confirms network metrics available
________________________________________
6. Disk usage (node level)
node_filesystem_size_bytes
👉 Validates node exporter is working
________________________________________
7. Node CPU
node_cpu_seconds_total
👉 Raw CPU metric for host
________________________________________
8. Check labels (VERY IMPORTANT)
container_cpu_usage_seconds_total{container_label_com_docker_compose_service="grafana"}
👉 Confirms correct label key/value
________________________________________
9. List all services (labels)
label_values(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total, container_label_com_docker_compose_service)
👉 Shows all container/service names
________________________________________
10. Check if Prometheus is scraping itself
up
👉 Shows status of all targets (1 = up)



📊 GRAFANA / GRAPH QUERIES (REAL USAGE)

👉 Use in Grafana panels or Prometheus Graph

 1. CPU usage per container
sum(rate(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total[1m])) by (container_label_com_docker_compose_service) * 100
👉 Shows % CPU usage per container
________________________________________
 2. Memory usage per container
sum(container_memory_usage_bytes) by (container_label_com_docker_compose_service)
👉 Shows memory usage per container
________________________________________
 3. Network RX per container
sum(rate(container_network_receive_bytes_total[1m])) by (container_label_com_docker_compose_service)
👉 Incoming traffic per container
________________________________________
 4. Network TX per container
sum(rate(container_network_transmit_bytes_total[1m])) by (container_label_com_docker_compose_service)
👉 Outgoing traffic per container
________________________________________
 5. Total CPU usage (host)
100 - (avg(rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[1m])) * 100)
👉 Overall system CPU usage %
________________________________________
 6. Memory usage % (host)
(node_memory_MemTotal - node_memory_MemAvailable) / node_memory_MemTotal * 100
👉 System memory usage %
________________________________________
 7. Disk usage %
(node_filesystem_size_bytes - node_filesystem_free_bytes) / node_filesystem_size_bytes * 100
👉 Disk usage %
________________________________________
 8. Load average
node_load1
👉 System load (short-term pressure)
________________________________________
 9. Active containers over time
count(container_last_seen)
👉 Track container count trends
________________________________________
 10. CPU usage (single container)
rate(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total{container_label_com_docker_compose_service="grafana"}[1m]) * 100
👉 Debug specific container

